---
import DocsLayout from '../../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro'
---
<DocsLayout title="Install BridgeAIChat Control Host" description="Install and run the BridgeAIChat gateway and hosted UI.">
  <section class="surface">
    <div class="eyebrow">Install</div>
    <h1>Set up the control host.</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      The control host runs the gateway and serves the web UI. In the current beta, the gateway also talks directly to
      the Tailscale API so the UI can list devices for the tailnet the user enters.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section-gap grid two">
    <div class="card stack">
      <div class="eyebrow">Release</div>
      <h2>Use the app archive</h2>
      <pre>tar -xzf bridge-app_v0.1.0-beta.1_darwin_arm64.tar.gz
cd bridge-app_v0.1.0-beta.1_darwin_arm64
bash install-app.sh</pre>
      <p>The packaged installer copies the gateway and UI into <code>~/.bridge-app/current</code> and installs a local launcher.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card stack">
      <div class="eyebrow">Dev</div>
      <h2>Run from source</h2>
      <pre>cd bridge-ai-app/gateway
go run ./cmd/gateway</pre>
      <p>This is the fastest way to verify changes locally before cutting a release archive.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-gap grid two">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="eyebrow">Required Env</div>
      <h2>Set the Tailscale API credentials</h2>
      <pre>export TAILSCALE_CLIENT_ID=tsid_xxx
export TAILSCALE_CLIENT_SECRET=tssecret_xxx
export TAILSCALE_API_BASE=https://api.tailscale.com/api/v2
export APP_URL=http://localhost:8080</pre>
      <p><code>APP_URL</code> should match the browser origin you use to open the UI.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <div class="eyebrow">Verify</div>
      <h2>Check the gateway</h2>
      <pre>bridge-gateway

# open in a browser
http://localhost:8080</pre>
      <p>Use the login screen to enter your tailnet. If the page loads but no devices appear, verify the Tailscale API credentials and tailnet value first.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
